INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (129,1,'2012-10-12 21:50:57','2012-10-13 02:50:57','<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Chocolate Chocolate Chip Muffins:</strong></span><strong></strong>\n\nNo, that was not a typo. This is a perfect breakfast if you need a wake-me-up or it\'s your time of the month. ;)\n\n<strong>Ingredients:</strong>\n\nMuffin liners\n\n1¾ cups all-purpose flour\n\n2 teaspoons baking powder\n\n½ teaspoon baking soda\n\n2 tablespoons cocoa powder\n\n¾ cup white sugar\n\n¾ cup baking chocolate chips, plus ¼ cup for the top of muffins (I use dark chocolate)\n\n1 cup milk\n\n⅓ cup plus 2 teaspoons vegetable oil\n\n1 egg\n\n1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n<strong>Directions:</strong>\n\nPreheat the oven to 400°F.\n\nAdd the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cocoa, sugar, and ¾ cup of the chocolate chips into a large bowl. Mix these ingredients.\n\nAdd the milk, vegetable oil, egg, and vanilla to the bowl. Mix well but remember that lumpy batter is good for muffins.\n\nGrease the muffin liners. Pour batter into each liner. It makes 12 muffins for the size of my muffin pan.\n\nAdd some of the remaining ¼ cup chocolate chips into each muffin.\n\nBake for 20 minutes or until a fork or toothpick comes out clean.\n\nYou may wish to spread a little butter onto the tops of the muffins.\n\n&nbsp;','Breakfast','','inherit','open','open','','42-autosave','','','2012-10-12 21:50:57','2012-10-13 02:50:57','',42,'http://mrscowherskitchen.oakwoodsystems.net/uncategorized/42-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(130,1,'2012-09-02 20:29:06','2012-09-03 01:29:06','','Breakfast','','inherit','open','open','','42-revision-6','','','2012-09-02 20:29:06','2012-09-03 01:29:06','',42,'http://mrscowherskitchen.oakwoodsystems.net/uncategorized/42-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(128,1,'2012-10-12 21:31:24','2012-10-13 02:31:24','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Chocolate Chip Cookies:</span></strong>\r\n\r\nBefore I start this recipe, I would like to inform you that this makes a rather large batch. I tend to half the recipe since I usually only bake for my husband.\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients:</strong>\r\n\r\n1 cup butter, softened\r\n\r\n1 cup white sugar\r\n\r\n1 cup packed brown sugar\r\n\r\n2 eggs\r\n\r\n3 cups all-purpose flour\r\n\r\n2 teaspoons vanilla extract\r\n\r\n1 teaspoon hot baking soda\r\n\r\n2 teaspoons hot water\r\n\r\n1/2 teaspoon salt\r\n\r\n2 cups baking chocolate chips (We prefer to use Hershey\'s Special Dark chips)\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions:</strong>\r\n\r\nAs always before beginning, you want to preheat your oven, in this case to 350° F.\r\n\r\nCream together the butter, white sugar, and brown sugar until smooth. Using a pastry cutter at first helps. Then I recommend using a spoon after it has smoothed a little.\r\n\r\nBeat in the eggs one at a time and then stir in the vanilla.\r\n\r\nDissolve the baking soda in hot water. (This gives the baking soda a head start to work, rather than simply adding baking soda straight into your mix.) Add the dissolved baking soda, as well as the salt, to the batter.\r\n\r\nStir in the flour (You\'ll now realize how much dough you are actually making) and chocolate chips. Nuts are always optional.\r\n\r\nDrop large spoonfuls of the dough onto pans. Despite what the original recipe says, I recommend greasing the pan, especially if you shop on a budget for kitchen supplies like I do.\r\n\r\nThe cookies will take anywhere from 10-15 minutes. Set the timer to 10 minutes to be safe. The time length will depend on how gooey or crunchy you like your cookies.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Cookies','','inherit','open','open','','95-revision-7','','','2012-10-12 21:31:24','2012-10-13 02:31:24','',95,'http://mrscowherskitchen.oakwoodsystems.net/uncategorized/95-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(59,1,'2012-08-28 00:24:09','2012-08-28 00:24:09','','Desserts','','inherit','open','open','','51-revision','','','2012-08-28 00:24:09','2012-08-28 00:24:09','',51,'h