d for muffins.\r\n\r\nGrease the muffin liners. Pour batter into each liner. It makes 12 muffins for the size of my muffin pan.\r\n\r\nAdd some of the remaining ¼ cup chocolate chips into each muffin.\r\n\r\nBake for 20 minutes or until a fork or toothpick comes out clean.\r\n\r\nYou may wish to spread a little butter onto the tops of the muffins.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Breakfast','','publish','closed','closed','','breakfast','','','2012-10-12 21:49:55','2012-10-13 02:49:55','',0,'http://mrscowherskitchen.oakwoodsystems.net/?page_id=42',0,'page','',0),(43,1,'2012-08-28 00:22:19','2012-08-28 00:22:19','','Music Corner','','publish','closed','closed','','my-music','','','2012-09-02 20:31:05','2012-09-03 01:31:05','',0,'http://mrscowherskitchen.oakwoodsystems.net/?page_id=43',0,'page','',0),(44,1,'2012-08-28 00:22:16','2012-08-28 00:22:16','','My Music','','inherit','open','open','','43-revision','','','2012-08-28 00:22:16','2012-08-28 00:22:16','',43,'http://mrscowherskitchen.oakwoodsystems.net/uncategorized/43-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(45,1,'2012-08-28 00:23:02','2012-08-28 00:23:02','My name is Karen Cowher. I\'ve been a Mrs. since June 11, 2012 and have loved every day of it. In order to accurately explain my life as a cook, I must first explain why and for whom I started cooking to begin with.\r\n\r\nOn November 10, 2011 I met a wonderful man named Robert Cowher. It was our first date, and I was a tad nervous. I didn\'t have much to say because of that and lack of self confidence, but I showed as much interest in him and gave as many smiles as I could. The date went rather well and he asked me at the end of it for a second date, scheduled for a week later. Our second date ended up being only three days later, though. We really started to click the second and third day. Soon after we were inseparable.\r\n\r\nIn our second week of dating, though it was probably our eighth date at that time, I decided to do something for Robert that I knew would show him that I wasn\'t about to walk away and was ready to show dedication. He had mentioned several times that he really appreciated a woman that cooked. The most cooking I had done was light baking, macaroni, pancakes and eggs, and the occasional basic pasta. I\'ve always been a picky person when it comes to food. I also never wanted to get married or even date, so learning to cook was of no interest and felt like no need for me. How quickly that changed.\r\n\r\nThe first meal I cooked for Robert was something I knew he would love and something I thought I had created on my own, though the second part proved to be wrong. I knew how much Robert loved bacon and really all types of meat. I decided I was going to make bacon and cheese wrapped pork chops. I used my mom\'s homemade mashed potatoes recipe and boiled some corn that came from my parents\' garden. I also made macaroni, which was more for my picky self, and biscuits. I requested that Robert stay in my bedroom while I cooked because I didn\'t want him to have a clue what I was cooking or to see me doing it in case I completely messed it up. I expected the pork chops to broil in the oven for at least an hour. According to Robert, he was waiting in my room, fortunately with one of his books, for three hours. To say the least, he was rather hungry when I finally brought him out to the living room.\r\n\r\nRobert thought the meal was amazing. To this day, he still will occasionally bring up how sweet he thought it was when he walked into the living room and saw that I had a cup of hot tea ready for him, without his asking me to do so. Sometimes simple gestures go a long way. Anyway, I also had a dessert for him. It didn\'t go very well and ended up more like pudding because I messed up the crust, but I had intended on giving him a chocolate cheesecake. An example of how sweet of a man I landed is how he reacted to the cheesecake. He said it was the best pudding he had ever eaten. :)\r\n\r\nSo that is how my journey with cooking began. I quickly got to where I was cooking breakfast and dinner for him every day we were together. We almost never went more than two days without seeing each other. He proposed to me on May 10, 2012 and we got married with seven of our family members present on June 11, 2012.\r\n\r\nI thoroughly enjoy cooking for several reasons. I enjoy trying new recipes and it is often relaxing. The main reason and that only one that matters, though, is that I love to see my husband\'s eyes widen and that big smile when he sees the plate I\'ve set in front of him. I will never grow tired of hearing his obvious appreciation and when he answers that yes, my meal is better than a certain restaurant\'s or family member\'s.\r\n\r\nLong story short, I cook for and because of my sweet handsome husband, but I also enjoy it very much.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','The Cook\'s Story','','publish','closed','closed','','whyicook','','','2012-09-02 20:31:15','2012-09-03 01:31:15','',0,'http://mrscowherskitchen.oakwoodsystems.net/?page_id=45',0,'page','',0),(46,1,'2012-08-28 00:22:23','2012-08-28 00:22:23','','Auto Draft','','inherit','open','open','','45-revision','','','2012-08-28 00:22:23','2012-08-28 00:22:23','',45,'http://mrscowherskitchen.oakwoodsystems.net/uncategorized/45-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(48,1,'2012-08-28 00:05:08','2012-08-28 00:05:08','','Recipes','','inherit','open','open','','42-revision','','','2012-08-28 00:05:08','2012-08-28 00:05:08','',42,'http://mrscowherskitchen.oakwoodsystems.net/uncategorized/42-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(49,1,'2012-08-28 00:24:01','2012-08-28 00:24:01','','Lunch/Dinner','','publish','closed','closed','','lunchdinner','','','2012-09-02 20:30:55','2012-09-03 01:30:55','',0,'http://mrscowherskitchen.oakwoodsystems.net/?page_id=49',0,'page','',0),(50,1,'2012-08-28 00:23:52','2012-08-28 00:23:52','','Auto Draft','','inherit','open','open','','49-revision','','','2012-08-28 00:23:52','2012-08-28 00:23:52','',49,'http://mrscowherskitchen.oakwoodsystems.net/unca