ms.net/uncategorized/51-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(90,1,'2012-08-30 01:56:03','2012-08-30 01:56:03','','Lunch/Dinner','','inherit','open','open','','49-revision-4','','','2012-08-30 01:56:03','2012-08-30 01:56:03','',49,'http://mrscowherskitchen.oakwoodsystems.net/uncategorized/49-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(91,1,'2012-08-30 01:57:10','2012-08-30 01:57:10','','Lunch/Dinner','','inherit','open','open','','49-autosave','','','2012-08-30 01:57:10','2012-08-30 01:57:10','',49,'http://mrscowherskitchen.oakwoodsystems.net/uncategorized/49-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(94,1,'2012-08-30 01:59:41','2012-08-30 01:59:41','','Cakes and Pies','','inherit','open','open','','92-revision-2','','','2012-08-30 01:59:41','2012-08-30 01:59:41','',92,'http://mrscowherskitchen.oakwoodsystems.net/uncategorized/92-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(95,1,'2012-08-30 02:00:07','2012-08-30 02:00:07','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Chocolate Chip Cookies:</span></strong>\r\n\r\nBefore I start this recipe, I would like to inform you that this makes a rather large batch. I tend to half the recipe since I usually only bake for my husband.\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients:</strong>\r\n\r\n1 cup butter, softened\r\n\r\n1 cup white sugar\r\n\r\n1 cup packed brown sugar\r\n\r\n2 eggs\r\n\r\n3 cups all-purpose flour\r\n\r\n2 teaspoons vanilla extract\r\n\r\n1 teaspoon hot baking soda\r\n\r\n2 teaspoons hot water\r\n\r\n½ teaspoon salt\r\n\r\n2 cups baking chocolate chips (We prefer to use Hershey\'s Special Dark chips)\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions:</strong>\r\n\r\nAs always before beginning, you want to preheat your oven, in this case to 350° F.\r\n\r\nCream together the butter, white sugar, and brown sugar until smooth. Using a pastry cutter at first helps. Then I recommend using a spoon after it has smoothed a little.\r\n\r\nBeat in the eggs one at a time and then stir in the vanilla.\r\n\r\nDissolve the baking soda in hot water. (This gives the baking soda a head start to work, rather than simply adding baking soda straight into your mix.) Add the dissolved baking soda, as well as the salt, to the batter.\r\n\r\nStir in the flour (You\'ll now realize how much dough you are actually making) and chocolate chips. Nuts are always optional.\r\n\r\nDrop large spoonfuls of the dough onto pans. Despite what the original recipe says, I recommend greasing the pan, especially if you shop on a budget for kitchen supplies like I do.\r\n\r\nThe cookies will take anywhere from 10-15 minutes. Set the timer to 10 minutes to be safe. The time length will depend on how gooey or crunchy you like your cookies.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Cookies','','publish','closed','closed','','cookies','','','2012-10-12 21:51:49','2012-10-13 02:51:49','',51,'http://mrscowherskitchen.oakwoodsystems.net/?page_id=95',0,'page','',0),(96,1,'2012-08-30 01:59:50','2012-08-30 01:59:50','','Auto Draft','','inherit','open','open','','95-revision','','','2012-08-30 01:59:50','2012-08-30 01:59:50','',95,'http://mrscowherskitchen.oakwoodsystems.net/uncategorized/95-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(98,1,'2012-08-30 02:00:07','2012-08-30 02:00:07','','Cookies and Muffins','','inherit','open','open','','95-revision-2','','','2012-08-30 02:00:07','2012-08-30 02:00:07','',95,'http://mrscowherskitchen.oakwoodsystems.net/uncategorized/95-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(99,1,'2012-08-30 02:01:00','2012-08-30 02:01:00','','Brownies and Other Goodies','','publish','closed','closed','','brownies-and-other-goodies','','','2012-09-02 20:30:12','2012-09-03 01:30:12','',51,'http://mrscowherskitchen.oakwoodsystems.net/?page_id=99',0,'page','',0),(100,1,'2012-08-30 02:00:49','2012-08-30 02:00:49','','Auto Draft','','inherit','open','open','','99-revision','','','2012-08-30 02:00:49','2012-08-30 02:00:49','',99,'http://mrscowherskitchen.oakwoodsystems.net/uncategorized/99-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(101,1,'2012-08-30 02:01:00','2012-08-30 02:01:00','','Brownies and Other Goodies','',